  <section>
    <h2>Feedback Page</h2>
    <p>
      The Feedback page (<a href="feedback.html" target="_blank">feedback.html</a>) was designed to collect user feedback in a structured, accessible way. It uses multiple HTML elements, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Form Elements:</strong> Inputs for name, email, telephone, address, and comments, using appropriate types (text, email, tel).</li>
      <li><strong>Validation:</strong> HTML5 validation with <code>required</code> attributes, input types, and <code>title</code> attributes for custom messages.</li>
      <li><strong>Character Counter:</strong> A character count paragraph for the comments field, dynamically updated by JavaScript (in FeedbackForm.js).</li>
      <li><strong>Dropdown and Multi-Select:</strong> A select menu for feedback topic and a multiple selection box for improvement suggestions.</li>
      <li><strong>Radio Buttons:</strong> To choose if users recommend the website.</li>
      <li><strong>Rating Input:</strong> Emoji radio buttons to rate the experience.</li>
      <li><strong>File Upload:</strong> Accepts images, PDF, and docx files.</li>
      <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> All inputs have associated labels and placeholders.</li>
      <li><strong>Styling:</strong> The form uses CSS for spacing, colors, and hover states to improve usability.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      I ensured that the page is accessible by including alt text, clear labels, and keyboard-friendly navigation.
    </p>
    <a class="button-link" href="validation_ST3.html#feedback-validation" target="_blank">View Feedback Page Validation</a>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Team Page</h2>
    <p>
      The Team page (<a href="team.html" target="_blank">team.html</a>) showcases the team members interactively. Its structure includes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Grid Layout:</strong> Each member is displayed in a styled box with image and details.</li>
      <li><strong>Hover Effects:</strong> Thumbnails are designed to be visually engaging on hover (this can be further improved with CSS transitions).</li>
      <li><strong>HTML Semantics:</strong> Proper use of headings, paragraphs, and lists to organize information.</li>
      <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> All images include descriptive alt attributes.</li>
      <li><strong>Responsiveness:</strong> The layout adjusts using CSS Grid or Flexbox (depending on CSS implementation).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The page adheres to the global styling and integrates with the site template for a consistent look.
    </p>
    <a class="button-link" href="validation_ST3.html#team-validation" target="_blank">View Team Page Validation</a>
  </section>

